has gotten into you?

956
01:03:37,075 --> 01:03:39,433
Nothing. Nothing.
Just-- Just--

957
01:03:39,592 --> 01:03:41,355
Dad, you can't
get married.

958
01:03:41,513 --> 01:03:43,272
It'll totally ruin
completely everything.

959
01:03:43,433 --> 01:03:47,432
Hal. Hal.

960
01:03:47,592 --> 01:03:49,949
Hallie.

961
01:03:50,110 --> 01:03:52,669
Don't look at me.
I don't know a thing.

962
01:04:06,905 --> 01:04:10,943
She thought I was going to adopt her?

963
01:04:11,103 --> 01:04:14,740
- Hi, doll.
- Hi.

964
01:04:14,900 --> 01:04:16,658
Oh, you look
stressed, baby.

965
01:04:20,378 --> 01:04:22,138
- How about a martini?
- How about a double?

966
01:04:22,298 --> 01:04:25,778
Coming right up.

967
01:04:25,937 --> 01:04:28,937
Chessy.

968
01:04:29,096 --> 01:04:32,175
Don't you love it? It's just what
we need. It's such a big house.

969
01:04:32,335 --> 01:04:34,212
Chessy!

970
01:04:36,813 --> 01:04:38,572
You rang?

971
01:04:38,732 --> 01:04:42,411
Two martinis, please.
And make Mr Parker's a double.

972
01:04:44,369 --> 01:04:47,529
Chess, please.
I'm getting a migraine.

973
01:04:47,690 --> 01:04:50,568
Mm-hmm.

974
01:04:50,728 --> 01:04:52,486
I told Hallie.

975
01:04:52,645 --> 01:04:54,407
You did?
And?

976
01:04:54,567 --> 01:04:56,965
She went ballistic.
She started yelling in French.

977
01:04:57,125 --> 01:04:58,884
I didn't even know
she spoke French.

978
01:04:59,043 --> 01:05:00,805
I don't know what's
gotten into her.

979
01:05:00,965 --> 01:05:04,321
Oh, Nicky. This reaction
is totally classic.

980
01:05:04,481 --> 01:05:07,283
It's "Daddy's Getting
Remarried 101."

981
01:05:07,442 --> 01:05:10,241
I'd be worried if
she didn't act this way.

982
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:13,120
Look. Why don't I
go talk to her?

983
01:05:13,280 --> 01:05:15,039
You know,
woman to woman.

984
01:05:15,199 --> 01:05:18,638
I-I think she's a little sensitive
about you right now.

985
01:05:18,797 --> 01:05:21,196
That's why
I need to do it.

986
01:05:21,357 --> 01:05:23,434
We've got to break
the ice sometime.

987
01:05:23,594 --> 01:05:26,235
Wear your shirt
like this.

988
01:05:26,395 --> 01:05:29,113
I like it when I can see
a little chest hair.

989
01:05:38,230 --> 01:05:40,149
Hm.

990
01:05:43,348 --> 01:05:45,987
Knock, knock.
Can I join you?

991
01:05:46,147 --> 01:05:48,066
Sure.

992
01:05:52,744 --> 01:05:54,506
Guess the news
of the engagement...

993
01:05:54,666 --> 01:05:56,824
- came as a bit of a shock, huh?
- Basically.

994
01:05:56,983 --> 01:06:00,343
You know, I remember
what it was like to be 11.

995
01:06:00,504 --> 01:06:03,541
I had my first beau at 11.
It's a wonderful age.

996
01:06:03,701 --> 01:06:05,979
You're just starting to feel
like a woman,

997
01:06:06,139 --> 01:06:08,899
and, believe it or not,
soon, you'll understand...

998
01:06:09,058 --> 01:06:10,818
what it's like
to be in love.

999
01:06:10,979 --> 01:06:12,738
Me?
I don't think so.

1000
01:06:12,898 --> 01:06:15,017
I don't even have
my 12-year-old molars yet.

1001
01:06:15,177 --> 01:06:17,096
Oh, well.
Take it from someone...

1002
01:06:17,255 --> 01:06:19,976
who got their molars
very early in life,

1003
01:06:20,136 --> 01:06:22,493
being in love is
a fantastic mystery...

1004
01:06:22,654 --> 01:06:24,652
that takes a man
and a woman--

1005
01:06:24,815 --> 01:06:28,451
I don't mean to be jerky when you're
trying to be all mushy and everything,

1006
01:06:28,610 --> 01:06:30,530
but I know what mystery
my dad sees in you.

1007
01:06:30,690 --> 01:06:32,771
You do?

1008
01:06:32,930 --> 01:06:34,889
You're young and beautiful
and sexy.

1009
01:06:35,050 --> 01:06:36,808
And, hey.
The guy's only human.

1010
01:06:36,969 --> 01:06:38,728
But, if you ask me,
marriage is supposed to be...

1011
01:06:38,889 --> 01:06:40,727
based on something more
than just sex, right?

1012
01:06:40,887 --> 01:06:42,646
Boy.

1013
01:06:42,806 --> 01:06:45,166
Your father
underestimates you.

1014
01:06:45,327 --> 01:06:49,044
But you won't,
will you, Meredith?

1015
01:06:49,206 --> 01:06:51,803
Being young and beautiful
is not a crime, you know.

1016
01:06:51,964 --> 01:06:55,484
And for your 411,
I adore your father.

1017
01:06:55,643 --> 01:06:58,641
He's exactly the kind of man
I always planned on marrying.

1018
01:06:58,801 --> 01:07:00,759
This is
the real deal, honey,

1019
01:07:00,920 --> 01:07:03,359
and nothing you do is going
to come between us.

1020
01:07:03,519 --> 01:07:05,279
Hate to break
it to you, angel,

1021
01:07:05,437 --> 01:07:08,118
but you are no longer
the only girl in Nick Parker's life.

1022
01:07:08,278 --> 01:07:11,157
- Get over it.
- If this is the real deal,

1023
01:07:11,316 --> 01:07:13,074
then my dad's money...

1024
01:07:13,234 --> 01:07:16,275
has nothing to do with you
wanting to marry him, right?

1025
01:07:16,434 --> 01:07:19,675
Okay, puss. You listen,
and you listen good.

1026
01:07:19,834 --> 01:07:23,152
I am marrying your father in two weeks,
whether you like it or not.

1027
01:07:23,311 --> 01:07:25,390
So I suggest you do not tangle
with me any more.

1028
01:07:25,550 --> 01:07:29,429
You are in way over your head.
Is that clear?

1029
01:07:31,067 --> 01:07:32,908
Crystal.

1030
01:07:38,227 --> 01:07:41,705
Martin, a refill, please.

1031
01:07:41,864 --> 01:07:44,145
You must have grown
three inches, I swear,

1032
01:07:44,305 --> 01:07:47,302
in six weeks.

1033
01:07:47,463 --> 01:07:50,223
- Lovely choice of wine, by the way, Martin.
- Thank you, sir.

1034
01:07:50,382 --> 01:07:52,461
May I have a sip?

1035
01:07:52,621 --> 01:07:55,299
I don't think
you're gonna like it.

1036
01:08:05,216 --> 01:08:09,255
Well, if you ask me, the bouquet is
a little too robust for a Merlot,

1037
01:08:09,415 --> 01:08:12,852
but, then again, I'm partial to
the softer California grape.

1038
01:08:15,613 --> 01:08:18,611
She learned about wine
at this summer camp?

1039
01:08:18,771 --> 01:08:20,572
She must have.

1040
01:08:26,930 --> 01:08:28,728
Darling, are you all right?

1041
01:08:28,889 --> 01:08:30,647
I had one sip too many,
I guess.

1042
01:08:30,807 --> 01:08:33,368
You know, Mother, I feel like
I could use a bit of fresh air.

1043
01:08:33,527 --> 01:08:36,365
W-Would it be okay if
I stepped outside for a moment?

1044
01:08:36,525 --> 01:08:38,284
Are-Are you okay?
Would you like me to go with you?

1045
01:08:38,443 --> 01:08:41,483
Oh, no, no, no. I'll be fine.
Just got a touch woozy, that's all.

1046
01:08:44,241 --> 01:08:46,002
Woozy, huh?

1047
01:09:05,954 --> 01:09:09,953
Um, yes, I'd like to place
a collect call to America, please.

1048
01:09:11,753 --> 01:09:14,591
Hello.

1049
01:09:14,750 --> 01:09:17,230
- What's up?
- Hal, I'm desperate.

1050
01:09:17,389 --> 01:09:20,348
- Dad's getting married.
- What do you mean, getting married?

1051
01:09:20,508 --> 01:09:23,229
I mean black tie, white gown--
the whole enchilada.

1052
01:09:23,388 --> 01:09:25,506
- What?
- The wedding's in two weeks.

1053
01:09:25,666 --> 01:09:28,387
So, if there's any hope of getting
Mom and Dad back together,

1054
01:09:28,548 --> 01:09:31,105
we've got to do it fast,
and I mean really fast.

1055
01:09:31,265 --> 01:09:34,145
Okay. So, Mom and I are going out
to the theatre tonight.

1056
01:09:34,304 --> 01:09:36,743
I'll-I'll drop the bomb on her
first thing in the morning.

1057
01:09:36,902 --> 01:09:38,741
Okay. Thanks.

1058
01:09:38,902 --> 01:09:41,621
- And, Hallie, hurry!
- Okay, I will.

1059
01:09:43,701 --> 01:09:45,498
Oh, excuse me, sir.

1060
01:09:45,659 --> 01:09:48,939
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh. Yes.

1061
01:09:49,098 --> 01:09:51,696
Now, what say you and I
take a little stroll...

1062
01:09:51,855 --> 01:09:53,697
in the park,
eh, young lady?

1063
01:09:53,858 --> 01:09:57,015
- Okay.
- Um. Now--

1064
01:09:57,174 --> 01:10:02,133
- Come on. What's this all about?
- Well, it's a long story.

1065
01:10:02,293 --> 01:10:05,372
Well, it's a very big park, and we've
got plenty of time, you know.

1066
01:10:05,533 --> 01:10:07,291
Well, first of all--

1067
01:10:23,407 --> 01:10:26,923
Just do it, sweet pea.

1068
01:10:34,602 --> 01:10:36,921
Darling, come in.
I just have to finish this sketch...

1069
01:10:37,080 --> 01:10:38,839
and FedEx it
off to Paris.

1070
01:10:39,000 --> 01:10:40,760
And then, how about you and I
go out to lunch...

1071
01:10:40,920 --> 01:10:43,079
and spend the rest of the day
getting lost in Harrod's, huh?

1072
01:10:43,239 --> 01:10:44,998
I can't, Mother.

1073
01:10:45,156 --> 01:10:47,358
Sorry. I-I have to go
out of town today.

1074
01:10:47,518 --> 01:10:49,516
Oh, you have
to go out of town?

1075
01:10:49,676 --> 01:10:53,276
And where, may I ask,
are you going?

1076
01:10:53,436 --> 01:10:56,994
- Annie. Annie.
- That's where I have to go.

1077
01:10:57,153 --> 01:11:01,471
- I have to go see Annie.
- I see. And where might Annie be?

1078
01:11:01,631 --> 01:11:05,152
In Napa with her father,
Nick Parker.

1079
01:11:12,829 --> 01:11:14,787
You're not Annie?

1080
01:11:14,946 --> 01:11:17,146
That would be correct.

1081
01:11:17,307 --> 01:11:19,666
You're Hallie?

1082
01:11:22,265 --> 01:11:24,024
I am.

1083
01:11:24,184 --> 01:11:26,422
Annie and I
met at the camp,

1084
01:11:26,581 --> 01:11:30,782
and-and we decided
to switch places.

1085
01:11:30,941 --> 01:11:33,819
I'm sorry,
but I've never seen you,

1086
01:11:33,979 --> 01:11:36,579
and-and I dreamt of meeting you
my whole life.

1087
01:11:36,739 --> 01:11:39,977
And Annie felt the exact
same way about Dad, so--

1088
01:11:40,136 --> 01:11:42,417
so, we sorta
just switched lives.

1089
01:11:42,577 --> 01:11:44,816
I hope you're
not mad,

1090
01:11:44,976 --> 01:11:47,255
because I love you so much,
and I just hope that one day...

1091
01:11:47,414 --> 01:11:50,414
you could love me as me
and not as Annie.

1092
01:11:52,012 --> 01:11:54,574
Oh, darling.

1093
01:11:54,693 --> 01:11:57,092
I've loved you
your whole life.

1094
01:12:04,727 --> 01:12:09,167
I've never been so happy
in my entire life.

1095
01:12:13,286 --> 01:12:16,565
So, l-- I guess you have
to switch us back now, huh?

1096
01:12:18,924 --> 01:12:21,723
Well, technically,
you belong to your dad,

1097
01:12:21,882 --> 01:12:24,642
and Annie belongs to me.

1098
01:12:24,802 --> 01:12:26,801
His-and-hers kids.

1099
01:12:26,961 --> 01:12:30,118
No offence, Mom,
but this arrangement really sucks.

1100
01:12:30,277 --> 01:12:32,200
I agree,
it totally sucks.

1101
01:12:32,359 --> 01:12:34,597
Then, I say we fly to Napa,
see Annie and Dad...

1102
01:12:34,756 --> 01:12:37,757
and work this
whole thing out.

1103
01:12:37,917 --> 01:12:39,875
And I say
you're right.

1104
01:12:40,035 --> 01:12:41,995
Not to worry, darling.
I'll take care of everything.

1105
01:12:42,154 --> 01:12:44,954
You're not to worry.
Okay?

1106
01:12:48,312 --> 01:12:50,752
I'm sorry.
I can't handle this.

1107
01:12:50,911 --> 01:12:53,829
I mean, I haven't seen or heard
from Nick Parker in over 11 years,

1108
01:12:53,990 --> 01:12:56,071
and suddenly I'm flying
halfway across the world to--

1109
01:12:56,230 --> 01:12:59,028
I'm not mature enough for this.

1110
01:12:59,187 --> 01:13:02,268
If the man didn't make me so nuts,
I'd still be married to him.

1111
01:13:03,986 --> 01:13:06,546
I mean, we came up with this arrangement so
that we'd never have to see each other again.

1112
01:13:06,705 --> 01:13:08,825
I mean, look at me, Martin.
Have you ever seen me like this?

1113
01:13:08,985 --> 01:13:10,743
- We-- I--
- Don't answer that.

1114
01:13:10,904 --> 01:13:14,064
I mean, what if he doesn't
recognize me?

1115
01:13:14,224 --> 01:13:16,502
No, don't answer that,
either.

1116
01:13:16,663 --> 01:13:19,461
So, Hallie said
he was a-- a hunk?

1117
01:13:19,622 --> 01:13:21,940
He was rather dishy.

1118
01:13:22,101 --> 01:13:24,978
He had a smile that made me go weak
at the knees, if you can imagine that.

1119
01:13:26,820 --> 01:13:29,537
- Okay, I'm all set, Mom.
- Great. Me too. Almost.

1120
01:13:29,697 --> 01:13:32,458
Mom, your-your suitcase
is like totally empty.

1121
01:13:32,617 --> 01:13:34,375
Oh, right.
Sorry.

1122
01:13:34,536 --> 01:13:37,415
Um, did you speak
to your father, dear?

1123
01:13:37,575 --> 01:13:39,335
Um, yeah. Yeah.
I just hung up with him, actually.

1124
01:13:39,494 --> 01:13:41,294
He said he's really anxious
to see you.

1125
01:13:41,453 --> 01:13:44,772
Anxious-nervous, like he's totally,
completely dreading it?

1126
01:13:44,932 --> 01:13:49,612
- Or anxious-excited, like he's looking forward to it?
- Anxious-excited, definitely.

1127
01:13:49,770 --> 01:13:52,130
- Oh.
- He said he'll meet us tomorrow at noon...

1128
01:13:52,289 --> 01:13:54,247
at the Stafford Hotel
in San Francisco.

1129
01:13:54,408 --> 01:13:56,608
My, my, my.
That's incredibly soon. Isn't it?

1130
01:13:56,768 --> 01:14:00,325
Well, um, why don't you run downstairs
and-- and gather up our tickets...

1131
01:14:00,486 --> 01:14:03,045
- from your grandfather while I finish up here.
- Okay.

1132
01:14:03,165 --> 01:14:06,404
Liar, liar.
Pants on fire.

1133
01:14:06,563 --> 01:14:09,123
- Shh!
- Oh, Martin. I have a really ridiculous,

1134
01:14:09,243 --> 01:14:11,083
somewhat childish request
to make.

1135
01:14:11,242 --> 01:14:13,801
Martin, you know that
you're more than a butler to me.

1136
01:14:13,922 --> 01:14:16,121
You're more like a lovable brother who
just happens to wait on us, and, anyway,

1137
01:14:16,280 --> 01:14:19,838
- I was wondering if--
- I would accompany you on the trip?

1138
01:14:20,000 --> 01:14:22,998
- Make it a bit easier for you?
- Would you, Martin? Thank you so much.

1139
01:14:23,157 --> 01:14:25,436
I'd be so grateful and you don't
even have to come as our butler.

1140
01:14:25,597 --> 01:14:27,638
- Just as a friend.
- Madam, I'd be honoured.

1141
01:14:27,797 --> 01:14:31,474
And may I say as a friend,
if I was seeing my ex...

1142
01:14:31,634 --> 01:14:33,755
after 11 years
and I had your legs,

1143
01:14:36,553 --> 01:14:37,751
I'd wear
this little baby.

1144
01:14:39,672 --> 01:14:41,671
You'll kill in it!

1145
01:14:48,068 --> 01:14:50,267
- Bye, darling.
- Wish me luck.

1146
01:14:50,427 --> 01:14:52,188
Good luck.

1147
01:14:55,026 --> 01:14:57,026
- Bye, Pop.
- Bye, Hal.

1148
01:14:57,187 --> 01:14:59,425
So you're coming to Napa
for Thanksgiving. Right?

1149
01:14:59,585 --> 01:15:01,863
I wouldn't miss it
for the world.

1150
01:15:02,023 --> 01:15:05,223
Bye.

1151
01:15:05,384 --> 01:15:08,863
- Oh, and say hello to your father for me.
- I will.

1152
01:15:18,178 --> 01:15:20,056
Airport, please.

1153
01:15:39,048 --> 01:15:41,289
Okay. They'll be here
any minute.

1154
01:15:41,449 --> 01:15:44,486
Now, be nice, Daddy.
He's everything you ever wanted...

1155
01:15:44,647 --> 01:15:47,208
for your little girl,
plus millions more.

1156
01:15:47,368 --> 01:15:49,326
Then you know
I'll be nice.

1157
01:15:51,407 --> 01:15:54,324
Oh! Okay. There he is...

1158
01:15:54,484 --> 01:15:57,844
with the whole
motley crew.

1159
01:15:59,163 --> 01:16:01,801
- Hi, darling.
- Hi.

1160
01:16:01,962 --> 01:16:04,560
Hallie, Chessy
and Sammy!

1161
01:16:04,722 --> 01:16:07,039
What in the world
are you doing here?

1162
01:16:07,200 --> 01:16:09,118
Honey, a dog
at the Stafford?

1163
01:16:09,278 --> 01:16:12,238
- Hal begged me to bring him.
- Oh, you're such a softy.

1164
01:16:12,398 --> 01:16:14,677
- Oh!
- Good doggy.

1165
01:16:14,837 --> 01:16:16,837
So, Meredith.
These the folks?

1166
01:16:16,996 --> 01:16:19,755
Yes. Mom, Dad.
You finally meet.

1167
01:16:19,915 --> 01:16:23,794
This is my fianc and the love
of my life, Nicholas Parker.

1168
01:16:23,953 --> 01:16:26,911
Hello, Nicholas.
I'm so pleased to meet you.

1169
01:16:27,072 --> 01:16:28,833
- I'm Vicki.
- Hi.

1170
01:16:28,991 --> 01:16:31,151
And this is Nick's
adorable daughter, Hallie.

1171
01:16:31,311 --> 01:16:34,430
This entire prenuptial get together
was her idea, I'll have you know.

1172
01:16:34,591 --> 01:16:36,389
How are you, young lady?
We've heard nothing...

1173
01:16:36,549 --> 01:16:40,669
- but wonderful things about you.
- Hello, pet.

1174
01:16:40,829 --> 01:16:43,546
You may call me
Aunt Vicki.

1175
01:16:54,303 --> 01:16:57,022
- Other end, madam.
- Oops!

1176
01:17:01,579 --> 01:17:04,177
- Yopes!
- That was a great flight. Wasn't it?

1177
01:17:04,338 --> 01:17:08,097
- I mean, it was so quick.
- I've never seen you quite so thirsty before, madam.

1178
01:17:08,257 --> 01:17:12,056
Well, would you believe, Martin darling,
I've never tasted vodka before this trip.

1179
01:17:13,176 --> 01:17:14,335
You could have
fooled me, ma'am.

1180
01:17:14,495 --> 01:17:16,413
Come on. Let's rock and roll.

1181
01:17:16,574 --> 01:17:19,574
I am in such
major trouble here.

1182
01:17:19,734 --> 01:17:22,611
If the hotel can do it, I think
that room is perfect for the wedding.

1183
01:17:22,772 --> 01:17:24,732
Not too big. Not too cramped.
And not that...

