01:31:18,946 --> 01:31:21,184
It's ours for the night.

1409
01:31:21,344 --> 01:31:25,984
Wow! So, how exactly
are we paying for this?

1410
01:31:26,143 --> 01:31:30,102
- Well, we pooled our allowances.
- Yeah. Right, Annie.

1411
01:31:30,262 --> 01:31:32,301
Okay.
Grandfather chipped in a bit.

1412
01:31:32,460 --> 01:31:35,738
- Annie.
- Okay. He chipped in a lot.

1413
01:31:35,899 --> 01:31:39,897
- Come on. You guys are gonna love it.
- Pretty snazzy.

1414
01:31:40,057 --> 01:31:44,776
Elizabeth and Nick,
your dinner awaits you.

1415
01:31:51,614 --> 01:31:53,373
Girls.

1416
01:32:00,371 --> 01:32:02,529
The table
is only set for two.

1417
01:32:02,690 --> 01:32:06,408
Oh, that's the other part
of the surprise.

1418
01:32:06,569 --> 01:32:10,446
- We're not joining you.
- You're not?

1419
01:32:10,606 --> 01:32:12,364
No, but I am.

1420
01:32:12,528 --> 01:32:15,564
Good evening. I'm Chessy,
and I'll be your server this evening.

1421
01:32:15,725 --> 01:32:18,565
- No wisecracks, please.
- And I'm Martin your sommelier.

1422
01:32:18,724 --> 01:32:20,683
May I offer you both
a taste of the bubbly...

1423
01:32:20,844 --> 01:32:22,602
in the hope that
you get a bit shnockered...

1424
01:32:22,762 --> 01:32:25,642
and not fire this lovely lady
and myself...

1425
01:32:25,801 --> 01:32:29,880
for following the orders
of these audacious 11-year-olds.

1426
01:32:30,039 --> 01:32:32,038
Annie, mood music,
please.

1427
01:32:36,156 --> 01:32:38,757
* I love you *

1428
01:32:39,956 --> 01:32:41,794
Just relax.

1429
01:32:41,954 --> 01:32:46,114
- * For sentimental reasons *
- Sail though time back to yesteryear.

1430
01:32:46,274 --> 01:32:49,912
* I hope you do believe me *

1431
01:32:50,073 --> 01:32:53,070
You do get all this,
don't you?

1432
01:32:53,231 --> 01:32:58,429
- Yes, I'm beginning to.
- * I'll give you my heart *

1433
01:32:58,589 --> 01:33:01,908
- They're recreating the night we met-- the boat,
the music-- - * I love you *

1434
01:33:02,069 --> 01:33:06,185
- The help.
- It's so sweet.

1435
01:33:06,345 --> 01:33:10,504
Martin, I think I'll take that drink.

1436
01:33:10,665 --> 01:33:12,944
Thank you, Martin.

1437
01:33:13,103 --> 01:33:16,542
Oh! Yeah.

1438
01:33:16,702 --> 01:33:21,940
- * And say we'll never part *
- To tell you the truth,

1439
01:33:22,101 --> 01:33:25,378
- I haven't been on a boat since the Q.E. 2.
- Neither have l.

1440
01:33:25,538 --> 01:33:29,137
Hmm? Well, then,
here's to, uh--

1441
01:33:29,298 --> 01:33:31,215
Our daughters.

1442
01:33:31,496 --> 01:33:35,055
Our daughters.

1443
01:33:37,454 --> 01:33:39,854
* Darling, I'm never lonely *

1444
01:33:40,014 --> 01:33:44,813
- Now I know how a goldfish feels.
- Ugh!

1445
01:33:44,972 --> 01:33:47,172
You know, sometime
if we're ever really alone,

1446
01:33:47,331 --> 01:33:50,171
maybe we could...
talk about...

1447
01:33:50,330 --> 01:33:52,890
what happened
between us.

1448
01:33:53,049 --> 01:33:57,408
It all feels a bit hazy to me now.
It ended so fast.

1449
01:33:57,568 --> 01:34:00,245
It started so fast.

1450
01:34:00,406 --> 01:34:02,568
Well, that part
I remember perfectly.

1451
01:34:05,285 --> 01:34:09,125
- * I've given you my heart **
- It looks like things are heating up quite nicely.

1452
01:34:09,284 --> 01:34:11,843
I'd say it's safe
to serve the vichyssoise.

1453
01:34:11,963 --> 01:34:14,402
You ladle,
I'll serve.

1454
01:34:17,560 --> 01:34:19,318
I'm sorry.

1455
01:34:23,678 --> 01:34:26,878
Yes, I'll...
uh, ladle.

1456
01:34:27,038 --> 01:34:30,515
Right.
And then I'll--

1457
01:34:30,674 --> 01:34:32,434
- Serve?
- Right.

1458
01:34:32,594 --> 01:34:34,354
Right.

1459
01:34:34,515 --> 01:34:39,992
So... you've done
fantastically well. Um...

1460
01:34:40,152 --> 01:34:43,991
your dream of owning your own
vineyard actually came true.

1461
01:34:44,150 --> 01:34:46,070
Mm-hmm. What about you?
You were always drawing...

1462
01:34:46,230 --> 01:34:48,789
on napkins
and corners of newspapers.

1463
01:34:48,948 --> 01:34:53,268
- Now you're this major designer.
- Yeah, it's great.

1464
01:34:53,427 --> 01:34:55,745
We both actually got
where we wanted to go.

1465
01:34:55,905 --> 01:34:58,186
Yeah, we did.

1466
01:35:00,384 --> 01:35:03,744
Anyway, what are we going
to do about the girls?

1467
01:35:03,903 --> 01:35:06,463
Well, now that they met,
we can't very well keep them apart.

1468
01:35:06,623 --> 01:35:09,742
Well, I could keep them for half of
the year, and then you could keep them.

1469
01:35:09,901 --> 01:35:12,461
- Well-- - Guys.
They can't go to two different schools every year.

1470
01:35:12,620 --> 01:35:14,539
- That's nuts.
- I agree.

1471
01:35:14,698 --> 01:35:16,539
Well, then, I could keep them both for
a whole year, and you could keep them...

1472
01:35:16,700 --> 01:35:18,458
- Liz.
- Hmm. Mm-mm.

1473
01:35:18,618 --> 01:35:20,376
- That's why we came up with--
- Mm-hmm.

1474
01:35:20,536 --> 01:35:25,255
Oh, G-- Sorry. Ignore me. Enjoy your soup.

1475
01:35:25,414 --> 01:35:28,215
That's why we came up
with the solution that we have.

1476
01:35:28,376 --> 01:35:31,053
Really?
I thought it was because...

1477
01:35:31,214 --> 01:35:33,614
we decided never to see
each other again.

1478
01:35:33,773 --> 01:35:36,091
Not we, Liz.

1479
01:35:36,252 --> 01:35:39,649
Well, you know, that part's become
a bit hazy to me, too, over the years.

1480
01:35:39,811 --> 01:35:44,088
- You don't remember the day you packed?
- No, that day I remember perfectly.

1481
01:35:44,248 --> 01:35:46,328
Did I hurt you when
I threw that, um...

1482
01:35:46,489 --> 01:35:50,006
- What was it? Uh, uh--
- It was... a hair dryer.

1483
01:35:50,165 --> 01:35:54,843
Oh, right. Sorry.

1484
01:35:56,884 --> 01:36:00,682
You know, I may never
be alone with you again.

1485
01:36:00,843 --> 01:36:05,561
So, about that day that you packed--
Why'd you do it?

1486
01:36:05,720 --> 01:36:07,879
Oh, Nick.
We were so young...

1487
01:36:08,039 --> 01:36:10,959
and we both had tempers.

1488
01:36:11,120 --> 01:36:13,837
We said stupid things
and so I packed.

1489
01:36:13,997 --> 01:36:15,957
Got on
my very first 747,

1490
01:36:16,116 --> 01:36:20,755
and... you didn't
come after me.

1491
01:36:20,914 --> 01:36:23,474
I didn't know that
you wanted me to.

1492
01:36:26,194 --> 01:36:28,191
Well, it doesn't
really matter any more.

1493
01:36:28,352 --> 01:36:30,992
So, let's just
put a good face on...

1494
01:36:31,151 --> 01:36:34,108
for the girls and get the show
on the road, huh?

1495
01:36:34,269 --> 01:36:37,588
Yeah, sure.
Let's...

1496
01:36:37,749 --> 01:36:40,227
get the show
on the road.

1497
01:36:46,025 --> 01:36:48,505
Your passport, Ms James.
Have a safe trip home.

1498
01:36:49,104 --> 01:36:50,423
Thank you.

1499
01:36:50,585 --> 01:36:54,103
- All set then. Where's Annie?
- I just rang up. She's on her way down.

1500
01:36:54,263 --> 01:36:56,022
Right.

1501
01:36:58,180 --> 01:37:00,260
So, I'll send Hallie
back to you over Christmas.

1502
01:37:00,422 --> 01:37:04,099
- And Annie will spend Easter with you.
- Mm-hmm.

1503
01:37:08,656 --> 01:37:11,098
Honey, what are you doing in those
clothes? We've got a plane to catch.

1504
01:37:11,257 --> 01:37:15,775
Here's the deal, Mom. We thought it over,
and we decided we're being totally gypped.

1505
01:37:15,935 --> 01:37:20,173
Dad promised we'd go on our camping
trip. And we want to go... together.

1506
01:37:20,334 --> 01:37:22,212
What camping trip?

1507
01:37:22,372 --> 01:37:24,532
The one we go on every summer
before school starts.

1508
01:37:24,691 --> 01:37:26,531
Annie, this is ridiculous.
Go upstairs and put your clothes on.

1509
01:37:26,692 --> 01:37:29,490
- Are you sure I'm Annie?
- Well, of course, I'm sure.

1510
01:37:29,651 --> 01:37:33,687
But, it's kind of hard
to be 100 %/% positive, isn't it?

1511
01:37:33,847 --> 01:37:37,007
Girls, this is totally unfunny.
You're gonna make your mother miss her aeroplane.

1512
01:37:37,168 --> 01:37:38,887
- Annie!
- Yes!

1513
01:37:46,602 --> 01:37:48,604
This one's Hallie.
I'm positive.

1514
01:37:48,763 --> 01:37:50,642
You know, I hope
you're right, Dad.

1515
01:37:50,803 --> 01:37:54,721
Because you wouldn't want to send the
wrong kid all the way back to England.

1516
01:37:54,881 --> 01:37:56,639
Would you?

1517
01:38:02,878 --> 01:38:06,158
Here's our proposition.

1518
01:38:06,317 --> 01:38:08,355
We go back to Dad's house,
pack our stuff,

1519
01:38:08,515 --> 01:38:11,154
and the four of us leave
on the camping trip.

1520
01:38:11,314 --> 01:38:13,873
- The four of us?
- And when you bring us back,

1521
01:38:14,034 --> 01:38:17,192
- we'll tell you who's Annie and who's Hallie.
- Or you do as we say,

1522
01:38:17,351 --> 01:38:21,990
and I take one of you back with me
to London whether you like it or not.

1523
01:38:27,947 --> 01:38:30,828
And what am I supposed to do
for three days? Sit home and knit?

1524
01:38:30,987 --> 01:38:33,347
Honey, we have kind of
a sticky situation.

1525
01:38:33,506 --> 01:38:38,465
- Sticky situation? What do you mean,
"sticky situation"? What exactly-- - Hmm-hmm.

1526
01:38:40,304 --> 01:38:42,422
Excuse me.
What is she doing here?

1527
01:38:42,585 --> 01:38:44,342
You see, that's part of the deal.
The four of us--

1528
01:38:44,502 --> 01:38:46,861
We... go together.

1529
01:38:47,020 --> 01:38:49,421
- What are you suddenly, the Brady Bunch? This is ridic--
- Hello.

1530
01:38:49,582 --> 01:38:51,380
Everything all right?

1531
01:38:51,540 --> 01:38:53,298
Well, no.
Actually it isn't.

1532
01:38:53,457 --> 01:38:56,378
I didn't realize that
you were going on this little outing.

1533
01:38:56,538 --> 01:39:00,256
- And to tell you the truth,
I'm not so sure that I'm okay with it. - I agree.

1534
01:39:00,415 --> 01:39:03,615
I think the ex-wife in
the next sleeping bag is a little weird.

1535
01:39:03,775 --> 01:39:07,934
- Thank you.
- I absolutely insist that you come with us. Really.

1536
01:39:08,095 --> 01:39:10,093
Liz--

1537
01:39:11,012 --> 01:39:12,012
No, honestly, Nick.
I've messed up your entire weekend.

1538
01:39:12,171 --> 01:39:15,731
It's the least I can do.
Really, please.

1539
01:39:26,248 --> 01:39:28,005
Dad, what's Meredith
doing here?

1540
01:39:28,166 --> 01:39:31,446
- Your mother invited her.
- What?

1541
01:39:31,605 --> 01:39:33,364
Be nice.

1542
01:39:45,281 --> 01:39:49,078
- Okay. All set? Have fun, everyone.
- What?

1543
01:39:49,238 --> 01:39:51,238
Liz, what are
you doing?

1544
01:39:51,398 --> 01:39:55,316
Well, I really think that you and Meredith
need some time alone before the big day.

1545
01:39:55,475 --> 01:39:57,355
Mom, come on!
That's not the plan.

1546
01:39:57,516 --> 01:39:59,676
Ah, honestly, you'll have
much more fun without me.

1547
01:39:59,834 --> 01:40:02,993
Wait, wait. If you're not going,
I certainly don't have to go.

1548
01:40:03,154 --> 01:40:04,914
I mean, trust me,
I'm not a big nature girl.

1549
01:40:05,073 --> 01:40:06,911
But this is your chance
to really get to know the girls.

1550
01:40:07,072 --> 01:40:09,712
I mean after all,
starting next week, they're--

1551
01:40:09,871 --> 01:40:11,630
they're half yours.

1552
01:40:17,268 --> 01:40:19,187
Have fun all of you!

1553
01:40:23,585 --> 01:40:25,344
Bye-bye!

1554
01:40:25,505 --> 01:40:29,344
Oh, I would pay big money
to see that woman climb a mountain.

1555
01:40:37,181 --> 01:40:39,341
Whoa!

1556
01:40:39,501 --> 01:40:42,898
- Come on, you guys.
- Whoa! Oh!

1557
01:40:56,133 --> 01:41:00,332
Oh, I'm gonna
kill my trainer.

1558
01:41:00,491 --> 01:41:04,291
He says I'm in such great shape. I can't
believe people actually do this for fun.

1559
01:41:05,930 --> 01:41:07,849
Hold on.
We're stopping.

1560
01:41:08,008 --> 01:41:11,209
Again? Dad, at this rate,
it'll take us...

1561
01:41:11,368 --> 01:41:13,126
three days just
to get to the lake.

1562
01:41:13,287 --> 01:41:17,286
Meredith isn't used to the altitude.
Just chill, okay?

1563
01:41:17,446 --> 01:41:21,566
Ooh.

1564
01:41:21,725 --> 01:41:24,444
Ah, I'm in serious pain.

1565
01:41:24,604 --> 01:41:28,523
Somebody hand me my Evian.
I can't move.

1566
01:41:28,683 --> 01:41:30,681
Sure.

1567
01:41:34,721 --> 01:41:36,478
Brilliant.

1568
01:41:41,158 --> 01:41:42,917
Here you go, Mer.

1569
01:41:50,873 --> 01:41:54,233
Honey, you okay?
What happened?

1570
01:41:54,393 --> 01:41:57,271
This little guy was
on her Evian bottle.

1571
01:41:57,431 --> 01:42:00,111
Oh, he won't hurt you,
Meredith.

1572
01:42:00,271 --> 01:42:02,509
Oh, right, right, right.
Right. I know.

1573
01:42:02,669 --> 01:42:05,789
You, uh, go ahead.

1574
01:42:05,949 --> 01:42:07,947
I'll be fine.

1575
01:42:08,107 --> 01:42:10,267
Get that thing away from me.

1576
01:42:10,508 --> 01:42:11,546
I hate things that crawl.

1577
01:42:11,707 --> 01:42:14,785
Aagh! How can you touch that?
Just put it down.

1578
01:42:14,944 --> 01:42:17,664
Okay. Okay.
I'll put it down.

1579
01:42:19,344 --> 01:42:22,663
- Girls?
- What? - What?

1580
01:42:22,822 --> 01:42:25,861
I'm going to take the lead. The two
of you help Meredith. All right?

1581
01:42:26,021 --> 01:42:28,581
Sure, you'll help me.

1582
01:42:28,701 --> 01:42:32,099
Right over a cliff,
you'll help me.

1583
01:42:32,258 --> 01:42:35,458
- Not a bad idea.
- Yeah. See any cliffs?

1584
01:42:35,619 --> 01:42:38,177
- Aah, my backpack.
- Need a hand, Mer?

1585
01:42:40,497 --> 01:42:45,773
Not from you, thank you.
Don't think I can't see right past those angelic faces.

1586
01:42:45,932 --> 01:42:47,694
One more trick from you two,
and I promise...

1587
01:42:47,854 --> 01:42:52,130
I will make your lives miserable
from the day I say "I do."

1588
01:42:52,290 --> 01:42:55,610
Got it?

1589
01:42:55,770 --> 01:42:59,090
Got it, Cruella.

1590
01:42:59,250 --> 01:43:02,047
What did you call me?

1591
01:43:02,207 --> 01:43:05,687
Nothing, nothing.
Not a thing, Cruella.

1592
01:43:05,847 --> 01:43:10,165
Oh, by the way, Mer, I think there's
something on your head.

1593
01:43:23,362 --> 01:43:27,558
Are you all right?

1594
01:43:27,719 --> 01:43:32,638
- Aah!
- What... happened?

1595
01:43:32,797 --> 01:43:36,634
Ask... them.

1596
01:43:42,555 --> 01:43:46,590
What did we do, Dad?
We were right behind you.

1597
01:43:50,269 --> 01:43:52,948
Here we go, girls.
This will hold us for a while.

1598
01:43:57,907 --> 01:43:59,988
Sure you don't want
some trout, Mom?

1599
01:44:00,147 --> 01:44:02,386
Is that okay, by the way,
if we start calling you mom?

1600
01:44:02,546 --> 01:44:05,705
I think your mother would prefer
if you called me Meredith.

1601
01:44:05,864 --> 01:44:11,102
And no thank you. I do not eat...
trout... for the thousandth time.

1602
01:44:11,261 --> 01:44:13,462
I will wait
until breakfast.

1603
01:44:13,623 --> 01:44:15,501
- What are we having?
- Trout.

1604
01:44:15,660 --> 01:44:18,141
Come on. It's part of the experience.

1605
01:44:18,301 --> 01:44:21,538
Mmm. And what's the other part?
Being eaten to death by mosquitoes?

1606
01:44:21,698 --> 01:44:24,138
God, you'd think
they actually like this stuff.

1607
01:44:24,299 --> 01:44:27,296
Well, what's that you're using?
Let me see that.

1608
01:44:30,656 --> 01:44:34,653
Well, you're gonna attract every
mosquito in the state with this stuff.

1609
01:44:34,813 --> 01:44:36,973
It's sugar and water.
Where'd you get it?

1610
01:44:38,973 --> 01:44:42,372
That's it. I am taking
one large sleeping pill...

1611
01:44:42,533 --> 01:44:44,450
and going to bed.

1612
01:44:50,968 --> 01:44:54,006
Meredith,
what are you doing?

1613
01:44:54,165 --> 01:44:57,446
I don't want the mountain lions to--

1614
01:44:57,606 --> 01:45:01,525
There are no mountain lions
up here, are there?

1615
01:45:03,203 --> 01:45:04,962
No.

1616
01:45:20,197 --> 01:45:21,956
Good night.

1617
01:45:26,275 --> 01:45:29,314
Girls, I'm telling you.
Lay off.

1618
01:45:29,473 --> 01:45:32,394
This isn't her thing, okay? I'm not
marrying her because she's Annie Oakley.

1619
01:45:32,553 --> 01:45:34,312
Who's Annie Oakley?

1620
01:45:34,471 --> 01:45:37,431
Just cool it.

1621
01:45:53,106 --> 01:45:55,305
Come on. Come on.

1622
01:45:55,466 --> 01:45:57,224
Okay.

1623
01:45:57,384 --> 01:46:00,582
I hope that
one large sleeping pill worked.

1624
01:46:07,821 --> 01:46:10,299
- You take that side.
- All right.

1625
01:46:13,337 --> 01:46:17,617
- Gosh, she's heavy.
- She's also like... snoring.

1626
01:46:25,531 --> 01:46:28,372
Nicky?

1627
01:46:53,962 --> 01:46:57,083
Sweet dreams, Mommie Dearest.

1628
01:47:11,756 --> 01:47:16,035
Mmm.
That feels nice.

1629
01:47:25,670 --> 01:47:28,870
Nicky!

1630
01:47:31,430 --> 01:47:34,509
Oh, man.

1631
01:47:34,668 --> 01:47:36,428
Ooh!

1632
01:47:42,785 --> 01:47:44,544
Ugh!

1633
01:47:47,264 --> 01:47:50,261
Ugh! Ugh!

1634
01:47:50,421 --> 01:47:53,301
- What's goin' on?
- Here's what's going on, buddy!

1635
01:47:53,462 --> 01:47:56,860
The day we get married is the day
I ship those brats off to Switzerland.

1636
01:47:57,021 --> 01:48:01,738
Get the picture?
It's me or them. Take your pick.

1637
01:48:03,938 --> 01:48:06,057
